OL,3,C'It's 15 months since he left that
OL,4,Croom:' Unpaid carers call for more
OL,5,Csupport
OL,7,FMichael Smith hasn't left his bedroom
OL,8,Fin fifteen months - and he's been
OL,9,Fhousebound for at least two years.
OL,11,FHis son, Paul, cares for him, a job
OL,12,Fwhich involves getting him ready in
OL,13,Fthe morning and for bed, organising
OL,14,Fhis medications, and preparing all his
OL,15,Fmeals. It's a demanding job which saw
OL,16,Fhim "reach breaking point," he
OL,17,Fexplained, "as much as you care for
OL,18,Fthe person."
